{"cursor":"25700","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\nAn 'endangered species' is a species of organisms facing a very high risk of\nextinction. The phrase is used vaguely in common parlance for any species\nfitting this description, but its use by conservation biologists typically\nrefers to those deigned Endangered in the IUCN Red List, where it is the second\nmost severe conservation status for wild populations, following Critically\nEndangered. There are currently 3079 animals and 2655 plants classified as\nEndangered worldwide, compared with 1998 levels of 1102 and 1197,\nrespectively.  The amount, population trend, and\nconservation status of each species can be found in the Lists of organisms by\npopulation.\n\nMany nations have laws offering protection to conservation reliant species: for\nexample, forbidding hunting, restricting land development or creating preserves.\n","linknr":647,"url":"Endangered_species","recorded":1362557282,"links":101,"instances":["medical","animal"],"pdf":["http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/summarystatistics/2012_2_RL_Stats_Table_2.pdf","http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/summarystatistics/2012_2_RL_Stats_Table_2.pdf"],"categories":["Endangered species|","Endangered plants|","Biota by conservation status","IUCN Red List","Environmental conservation","Habitat (ecology) terminology","IUCN Red List endangered species"],"headings":["Conservation status","IUCN Red List","Climate change","Conservation","Gallery","See also","Notes","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5b/Bufo_periglenes2.jpg/90px-Bufo_periglenes2.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/18/Status_iucn3.1.svg/240px-Status_iucn3.1.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fc/Padlock-silver.svg/20px-Padlock-silver.svg.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/41/Siberischer_tiger_de_edit02.jpg/250px-Siberischer_tiger_de_edit02.jpg","//bits.wikimedia.or